reviews.text: Beautiful place. Very calm n quiet. Cool Air coming from the Sea. Lots of trees and plants were placed here.

It's a wonderful place. There are lots of contemporary rock sculptures outside the museum in a garden like atmosphere. The auction of few artworks in the Kochi Biennale will take place here. It also has a great view of the Arabian Sea. The building is pretty old and maintenance works are also going on. Main attraction for me were the unique rock sculptures outside the bungalow.  There is ample parking space outside the venue.

Although it's near the fortkochi beach, its an unnoticed place .. actually the bungalow is now taken care by govt .. u can enter inside the compound but not inside the bungalow.. the premises of the bungalow has a very serene atmosphere with lot of sculptures and trees.. use the ramp or stairs to go to the view point .. from there u can get a nice view of the beach , L and G terminal etc.. not at all a busy place...
Perfect place to enjoy calm and quiet evenings. Near to Fort Kochi beach but away from the crowd. A really peaceful place to hide out.
Good place to visit. Most of the visitors were foriegners. Good view from here to the lagoon.
Legendary place. A must see for those interested in the history of Cochin kingdom.
Good place to visit. Historic place. Good place for students to learn about old history. Staffs are good at explaining briefly.

Historic palace that has been extensively renovated and is part of the Muziris heritage tourism circuit. This is the palace of the Paliyath Achans, who were Dewans or administrators for the kings of the Cochin royal family. Re-enactments of scenes from the life of its one-time inhabitants can be selected and played back on video screens set up in different parts of the palace. The palace and videos and artefacts gives one a feel of history.
Great historical place have to vist here one day
Very good palace maintained  by muzhris authority
Awesome.Just loved the ambience. Good for morning and evening walk. Can spend some good time with family and acquaintances.Less crowded from 7.30pm.
Nice and calm place. Kids can enjoy on the lush green grass and elders can walk around and spend time without any disturbances. Very good place to spend your evenings in the middle of city.
Good place to hang out. Ample space to spend time with friends and family. There is toilet facilities for freshup.

This is really an awesome place. I would like to add one suggestion is that the toilets are closed when I visited the place on 17 march 2019.  Really bad experience.. need to improve this otherwise the beautiful place will be distroied

Durbar Hall ground is a very nice place to spend your evening with your friends or family. The stadium situated at the ground is a very famous venue  for various types of art forms like dance , music etc. It is highly recommended as  a safe place for foreigners   to spend their evening. The temple nearby is in the name of Lord Siva. Various types of karnatik music and instrument music are also conducted there periodically.

a very nice place for a hangout with friends and family.. Had a great time here.. good infrastructure and eco friendly.. lot of area to explore and will get a natural feeling.. many movie shooting takes place here.. and this is a historic museum in which you can explore the historical things and an old palace..

Had a great time and thought it's bit old and the government not maintaining it properly then also enough things to see. It got the palace Museum,gardens,etc. Completely enjoyed my time had fun with my friends here.
Also the place is so near to the regional passport office so if you are coming there do have a visit here also.

Its a different  experience  it's  a heritage palace. There is a heritage museum well maintained.  Good greenery fresh air. We can understand about the ancient rulers and their life and ruling style. We will get an idea about the wars weapons they used to protect the citizens from the enemies. We can compare the political rulers and realise what a ruler should do the benefit of the citizens and salutes them.  It's wonderful experience.

This place has the ultimate potential to be a great public point of interest, but lack of public attention cause it a non worthy holiday spot. 

Some of the big sculptures are almost grounded and sitting benches are dirty. The place is perfect and almost isolated from city noise and pollution. Tons of big trees that are giving perfect ambience for hot days. The most visiting demographic are the youths.

Good museum signifying the whole dynasty of the rulers. But to reach the museum the visitor will have to walk a lot (climb stairs).
All in all a good place to visit for 2-3 hours and then roam around the place (park and greenery) and relax on the chairs provided on the way.

Recently Renovated fort is the remains of hr british era that prevailed in kochi. The fort although a simple standing structure was of importance back in time. The fort also has. View of the pallipuram fish trading centre.

Apart from the walled structure, there is nothing much to see.

Very well maintained

Monday holiday. Other days from 9.30am to 4.30pm
A big three storied building. This is the first European building in India
Nothing special but well conserved. Nice to visit the eldest building in India
Wonderful and a ameture place but the fort is amazing to see
Wonderful church. Inside the campus i feel like am in  some foreign church.i felt like to stay there  for more time. Because of my tight schedule i couldn't stay more than 30min.....
Nice cathedral. It's in pretty good condition so it must be looked after very well. Nothing too special though. You won't regret it if you miss out on it.

This Cathedral is one of the main tourist attractions in Fort Kochi. It is nice to see it, you should definitely go inside, it's a special place. If you have the chance, better go during the afternoon, they use red lights inside, so you can see it through the windows, it is something nice to see (See pictures attached in this comment). 
Please, don't expect a huge European Cathedral, because it is not!!

Very superb and clam place, still this church looks like new after so many years. 
You will fascinate with the beauty of the church.. but main problem they don't have parking facility as church is located in one of the main road where vehicle moving frequently,  but I went on week days nobody is their to give me info about the place as most of the church have somebody to give you information about the church if your are interested.
If you going for Kochi dont miss this place.
Beautiful church with an even more beautiful history. Never get tired of admiring it, both from the outside and the inside. Make it a point to see this church if you are in Fort Cochin.

One of the lesser visited places I suppose. Nobody really suggests to go here, and probably for good reason. It has an entrance fee of 20rs for Indians and 40rs for foreigners, but there's only like 4 rooms worth of artifacts in there. Photography is prohibited, so that makes it an even lesser of an attraction. You could probably cover it in 10 minutes or under.
A place having so much history! The handmade maps and designs are mind boggling! The detail in it is unbelievable. The dresses from so long back, and canopies and much more is fun to see!
Crosses, statues, clothing in a newly built house. How is that a museum of any sort. An old map of travancore from the 1800s is the only thing I liked there.
Nice maintained but will be a short tour as there isn't much to see beyond the main room.
It's a small museum, if you like to ponder over things still wouldn't take you more than an hour.

The food served here is pretty good. But i am not a fan of their cold coffees which seems to be watery. Also you end up having to make your own drink. But you should definitely try any of the food on the menu and I'm sure you would leave here a happy person.

Very expensive. I only ordered the chocolate cake and a few drinks. Everything was delicious, no doubt about that. The juices were very fresh. The cake is kind of very big for one person😅 not complaining 🤭. Overall a good place with a very cozy Vibe to spend the evening with a bunch of friends.❣️
Very beautiful ambiance. Went early in morning yet staff was well dressed and attentive.  Very less waiting time between orders.  Amazing taste. Bit extensive Yet Totally worth it.

Great ambience..  Great taste..  Great hospitality..  Must visit place..  Might have to wait a bit as there is too much people wanting for a seat..  But its worth the wait...  Speedy service.  Always full of foreigners..

What a place this is! An old courtyard house adaptively reused as a cafe, a perfect example of how a domestic place of historic value can be used creatively. The food is always good. Ate there twice and never disappointed. They can sometime take a little longer than u expect, but it is worth the wait totally! Best part is they open at 8:30 am

This Museum located bang on the highway is a must visit place for travelers to get a slice of Kerala s rich heritage and history. The exhibits are well arranged and one can understand and appreciate what Kerela was right from  Trading times when Vascodagama set foot on Kochi  and contributed in no small measure to the trade.

Loved the experience. Especially the art gallery which showcases mind blowing masterpieces from renowned artists. I visited this place with french contemporary artist Nadia russel. Even she was so excited after the visit.
Showcases the culture, tradition and history of Kerala...Superb ambience...The way they showcases these cultures is different and great..
Some interesting pieces of Indian art and dolls along with a historical exhibition depicting the history of Kerala.   Well worth a visit if you're in the area

The Museum of Kerala History is the oldest gallery in the Kerala Museum. It recounts the history of the state of Kerala through 36 dioramas on key historical episodes and personalities from the region. A light and sound show is organised for all visitors to the gallery, with commentaries in English and Malayalam. 
Sculptor Karamana Rajagopal of Thiruvananthapuram created the sculptures and dioramas in this gallery, and pre-eminent Kerala historian A. Sreedhara Menon extended advice on content.

Outside the gallery is a statue of Parasurama, the sage who is believed to have brought forth the land of Kerala from the ocean.

This was an interesting tour. We went over by canoe and were shown workers male & female exhibiting old skills such as rope making and wicker work. Lunch was nice and it is a lovely setting We were taken back by motorised rickshaws, now that’s an adrenaline rush!

You can book a guide , boat and an entire tourism package which shows you the culture of the village with local sea food. Plan in advance while coming to visit this place.can be covered in 4-5hrs. The people here provide great hospitality.
Also a famous Malayalam movie was shot here.
Ya.. Its good.. But there is no road transport we need our own vehicle. We can explore natural village beauty
God’s own country’s heaven is Kumbalangi. An exotic place to spend holidays and explore the village tourism.
More famous after a movie by its name is released...

The many stalls and the variety in them is a sigh to behold. If you have kids then it is a must visit for the rides and games that are put up in the fair. the many nurseries too are worth if you are a plants person. plastic shops offer so many products at cheap prices and so do the terracotta shops. you have to bargain with the terracotta vendors to get it for cheap.

Devotees place. I went to Aluva river to take a dip. Peaceful place. Beware of the depth when you are getting down. Some places there is surfaces where we can stand. But still. Be careful. Only go with a well trained swimmer.
I love this place.. Spiritual place and the beauty of periyar.. Calm and quiet place for evening walk.. A good place for family.. Peace of mind. 👍👍
Nice place for worship & entertainment. Less basic facilities. But,you can enjoy 🏊 & bathing with better security in periyar river.
Clean place. Easy to assess from the main road. Only crowded for 1 or 2 months during Shivaratri festival time.
Amazing place. But try to visit terrace to see real black stone idols. First floor idols are of white marble
Nice peaceful place to visit. Especially the time when thousands if pegions roam around the temple and land for a feast. A must visit place. Be there around 12 noon and see the wonder.
If you are curious to know the Jain way of living, this is one of the best place, where they give you guided tour (I don’t know whether it is always done). A serene place
Calm and historic place in palakkad. Located in jaini medu.
It's the only one kochi which you can see near by in between fortkochi & mattancherry.

Peaceful place. Everyone loves to visit, even locals loved it. 
Gurudwara is for everyone and anyone can visit it anytime.

This Gurudwara is one of the few Sikh temples in the southern Indian city of Kochi and attracts good number of Sikh devotees particularly on weekends and Gurupurabs. Located in a not-so-wide alley in near the posh locality of Panampilly Nagar. The Gurudwara is a blessing for people like me and my wife from North and currently residing in Kochi.
The one and only Gurdwara in Kerala

It's best place to be . Every religion people are invited.

Langar - 2.00pm to 3:30 pm

Blessful church.

Prayer is our direct line with heaven. Prayer is a communication process that allows us to talk to God! He wants us to communicate with Him, like a person-to-person phone call.

The definitive architecture will hit like "wow" 
For the visual appeal. But inside, it is a design disaster from audio point of view. You feel like you are inside a cave due to the dull echo from its walls. I wonder who designed this masterpiece of design flop?  Surely some latin christian architecture who is a close relative of a bishop or some powerful priest. 

All that apart, the novena to mother mary of perpetual help is very powerful and is attended by thousands on Saturday
Holy place. You will feel the divine power when you are in there

St. Francis Assisi Cathedral, Ernakulam is the seat of the Latin Catholic Archdiocese of Verapoly. The Cathedral is also known as 'Kappal Pally' (Ship Church) in Malayalam due to its distinctive architecture resembling a Ship.

Mass Timings 
Holy Mass Timings

Weekdays:  6.00 am, 7.00 am, 5.30 pm
Saturday :   6.00 am, 7.00 am, 11.00 am, 6.00 pm, 7.15 pm (English)
Sunday : 5.30 am, 7.00 am, 9.00 am, 5.30 pm

Our most Beautiful Church.
Specifically Constructed Ship like Architecture, by 
Contractor Mr P P George Uncle.
Also known as Kappalu palli for its structure.

This is the Cathedral Basilica church of Ernakulam-Angamaly Archdiocese. The church is having a good ambience. It also have an adoration chapel nearby. The painting at the altar is a attraction of this church. The bishop house is located near to this church. The church is having a well maintained parking. It is equipped with 2 A/C and 1 non AC hall which is capable of conducting marriage functions

The present church was built in the early twentieth century under the direction of Mar Aloysius Pazheparambil and was elevated to the status of a Basilica by Pope Paul VI on 20 March 1974.[4]

The large, tall and spacious cathedral has an altar that was used by pope John Paul II, when he visited India during 7 February 1986. The altar depicts the birth, the crucifixion and the resurrection of Jesus Christ. The two 68-foot tall towers in the front have statues of St Peter and St Paul on top, and the bell tower (88 feet high) has St. Thomas statue on top. There is also a depiction of Jesus's apparition to St Thomas.
Good place to pray... Adoration chapel could have been made AC...so we would get more peace inside it to pray peacefully

St.Mary's Cathedral in Ernakulam is one of a olden Church in Basilica standard. Near High Court junction, on Church Road this Basilica Church giving divine blessings to the Kichin people. The arts and design of the church is wonderful. Inside layout is very beautiful. Seats are very comfortable. We can feel a divine peace inside of the church. Really, St Mary's blessings showered on every devotees who comes with faith on this Divine Mother.
 Plenty of Car parking available. Perpetual adoration chapel is in front of the church. All kinds of catholic religions articles are available in front of the church.
   Very good place for come with family. Good.

Large parking area
A place having amalgamated worship of traditional kerala festival  and islamic Sufi taught.

Lot of space in spiritual ambience.spacious parking space.vast area prayer hall.more than 10 masjid contraoled under kanjiramattom  jamahath  . Peoples are living  without worry Here. very familiar mosque in kerala.more than centuries old masjid.
Very peaceful place and feels blessed. A good calm and great place to visit with family
Really spiritual place.. Feels blessed.. Women can also pray there in a seperate side.

One of the famous mosque. Even believers from neighbouring states visists here for religious beliefs and festivals. The festival named as kodikuth is a famous one in Kerala. Even other religious believers visists here for mental refreshment and prayer.

We can see a good atmosphere here with lots of art programs and cultural events  are going regularly. Temples and Churches are near. Travelling is also easy from here to anywhere. Peoples will get private bus and KSRTC bus to anywhere and also Metro station is here for the convenient travelling. Peoples will get all things in the shops here.

Good place to spend your leisure time. Every age group comes here. But the most are young children and senior citizens. Good place for exercises, evening walks and there are plenty of play area for children. The park is an elliptical shaped area with paved elliptical area for walks. It also stages musical and informative programmes.

Good place to spend your evening. There is a small children play area,you can spend time there by playing cheese, and others board games, equal enjoyable for both young and elderly people. There is an open theater where you will be able to enjoy drama, dance program, kathakali other cultural program. Even if you what to be alone in middle of all these you can find peace and jog around the park
One of a unique park both for children and elders. They provide some art shows very day without any fee. Everyone can also play chess and carroms in the evening.
Changampuzha Park is very poetic and beautiful place to spend. There is something for everyone to learn about writers and literature.

A great place for bird watching and can be visited at any time of the year. Boat rides are the highlight of the sanctuary. The migratory birds start arriving between December and January, perhaps the best time to visit. Weekends could probably get busy.

The wild inside a crowd😻
A calm green plot for evenings of busy life, fresh air, birds and the beauty of nature👌
Mangalavanam is very nearer to the High court and Marine drive.
We can spent time there between 9.00 AM & 5.00 PM.
A good population of mangroves makes this Bird sanctuary even more special.
But the area is not that much maintained and the paths inside the bird sanctuary are not good to walk.
Even though we can enjoy the peace of mind there👌

- Good place with natural beauty.
- The place is not able to justify its bird sanctuary tag.
- only local visitor birds ( like cormorants, lapwing,  Stilt etc) and resident birds are found here. 
- Small and median egrets are common here.
- Purple moorhen is also common.
- Bird watching tower and guides are not available here.

If you wanna go back to your old times or if you wanna feel fresh air and calm in the middle of city you should visit this place. Cause this place is capable to provide those. Well it's opens at 9 am to 5 pm.its close to high court and marine drive. It's a better place to bring young kids and family. If you are nostalgic about your village life you may visit this place. If the authority could take Care of this place it may look more beautiful because it's ain't have proper path to walk. But I just felt soo relaxed when I visited this place
Very clam and quiet place... Will suggest there for morning and evening walk... There is not much birds there to see.. but the place is too good

Serene and peaceful. The resort is very close to the river and is a perfect place for retreat. The staffs are very cordial and service oriented. The food served us very delicious. The management seems very committed to keep the facility in good shape. The building doesn't look that old. The whole resort is well maintained. Ideal for one night stay. The landscape is very beautiful.

Good service and good staff. Buffet lunch should have more non veg options. Just two non veg items is sad. Rooms are pretty good. Offer good fun team building activities by the staff if your looking for one. Good pool. And good scenic view from the resort as well.

Recommended.
No 5 star rating only because the climate is not enjoyable during summer days like a hill station. Its really hot. But the resort is too good with quality service and facilities. 
Employees are very friendly with a ready to help attitude.
Lot of indoor games, swimming pool, river access etc are main attractions.
Rooms are maintained really well and independent garden space/walk area.
Barbecue hut and river view dining huts available.

A bit too far from the city. Roads are a bit narrow near the resort. Calm and quiet place, perfect to take a break from the busy city life. The food was good, and the staff were very helpful. Excellent service overall.

No words to experience. Staff.. Rooms.. Cosy resort..Food..everything must say is top class and as good as a 4 star service. Staff over there were very welcoming and made the environment feel homely. All these good facilities was experienced by my team who were part of the team outing. It's not easy to satisfy such a huge crowd and I think they were professional enough to deal with very patiently. Must say all the staffs are caring and helpful. Thank you all for the wonderful experience.

A beautiful evening can be made further beautiful by visiting Cherai beach... Sunset is the beauty of this place😍 Early morning walks are priceless and you can spend the whole day at this place itself when you make a visit.. Hotels are likely to costly.. But affordable.. You can make a clear plan by booking hotel and visiting this place.. One of the best place for holiday plans.. You can enjoy nature to the fullest... Surfing also available at this beach so that you can make some adventurous moments of your life... If gone in pair, please do visit by earning morning around 5 30 am and evening by 5 pm.. That's the time where you can enjoy nature to the fullest and you will get a complete state of mind.. 
Food cleanliness are maintained in a proper way and most of the foods are  hygienic..
Enjoy the beauty of Arabian sea and Kerala.. God's own country😇
Here are some photos by myself taken are attached...
Awesome beach. Best time to go is between 6am to 9 pm. Its not hot in summer. Tides are slightly high and water is amazing. Cleanest beach around
I still love things that you don't even need to pay for. Going to Cherai beach and being around five of your friends and having a good time means so much more than going out and spending money...!

Wonderful long beach with lot of huge waves at times. Every one can enjoy there with the warm windy atmosphere. U can do kite flying. Kites available at nominal cost. Better avoid food items from there. Bring ur own food if possible.
Good ambience, clean and neat... Ample parking space and resorts. Best place to spend an evening with family. Although swimming in the sea is not recommended.

Good walking through the area..  Gives a feel of forest.. The park opens by around 8:30-9:00. If we enter by that time,  the full circuit will be over by 11:30.

Kids will enjoy a lot...

We can have walk for few distance through forest and the river view and the elephant bathing pool is another attractions on this place.

This is a nice place if you are interested in seeing elephants in your close range. This facility helps government to detain elephants when it requires. Wild elephants which creates issues with villagers, domestic elephants which caught in different law suits and wild elephants which are found seriously injured will come here. The wild elephants will get training here and will become domestic elephants. You can get very close to elephants which are already friendly. You can also see the elephant bath if you come early morning. 

There are few deers as well in this facility. There are plenty of space for people to walk around under the shades of greatly maintained greenery. Small cafeteria, children's play area and toilet facilities are also there. I didn't liked the toilet area much as the door knobs were not in place and also there were lot of water pooled here and there. 

The car parking  facility is good enough. You can park your car with peace of mind. The employees are very friendly.

Nice tourist place in ernakulam district near perumbaavoor. Nature friendly eco tourist place on the shore of periyar river. While plan to visit specially note that its not a monday. In this elephant training center monday is holiday

Really good meat! Try the tenderloin beef with Gorgonzola sauce - it's fantastic! 

Of course it is not a very cheap restaurant, but the quality of food and the service is just exceptional compared to most nicaraguan places. It is also one of the few places I drink regulary red wine.

Very friendly/polite staff!

Out of the three good vegetarian restaurants at kadavanthra junction, this one is the most affordable. Service is usually quick and the place is almost never completely empty but they have enough seating capacity to handle the rush. The rates of food are average and what you can expect from a normal veg only place. They serve food from early morning onwards. The food is okay but nothing to write home about. Their tea and coffee is, however, excellent and sometimes I even find myself ordering a second coffee after dinner...

Very nice and tasty vegetarian foods. They keep the standard of taste the same every time you go there. Hand wash area is too cramped and no tissues kept around. Bit meatless there. Parking is a concern as it is very near to Kadavantra junction.
Good food .But little expensive.Very close to Thampanoor Bus stand and Railway station .Good ambience and good service  Masala dosa is very good
Veg restaurant which serves at a reasonable rate. Peaceful ambience and good food. Breakfast and lunch s re great here.
Best vegetarian restaurant in the area with food at cheap price and great variety.

I would give marks to the food and the service. Both are good.
The hotel being an old one lacks a bit of cleanliness, but it's not dirty. For some it might not meet the expectations.

A great eatery which still has managed ti retain a lot of goodness from the yester years and right smack in the middle of a bustling metro. Full five points for the quality and old world charm. Hope to see it stay this way for the years to come.
We have been here since our childhood, simple restaurant with lots of nostalgic memories, same old noisy but friendly crowd from neighborhood, a place that spans decades, no 4 wheeler parking.
Idiyappam with mutta Curry and porotta with chicken roast..delight cuisines these two
Specialty : Portta and beef fry

The hotel is an interesting feature of the hotel. Cleanliness and pureness are important. All resources are available here. Especially biryani ... we go every day. All of you come and welcome everyone.
Mutton Roast was really nice in taste. We tried to order Mutton Biryani but it was finished by then. Felt that, need to visit during lunch to get it.
Best in the area. Jam packed , serves mouth watering food , especially beef roast and ghee rice. Biryani is good
Excellent chicken biryani. They serve it with a special pulinji type paste of tamarind and dates. Went well with chilled 7Up on a hot day. Service was slow but worth the wait.
The one place I will recommend to all my friends. Best know for its beef dishes. I simply love this place
Nadan food not so good and  Birayani is the Best

The food served here is okay and the quantity and quality both are not that good  but the staff here is very friendly and polite. The sitting area is  very spacious and because of the metro work the restaurant nowadays doesn't have so much crowd but before it was very crowded. If looking for good food then this is not the place😅

Very bad experience from this restaurant. I order a fresh pure orange juice without sugar. After waiting for 5 min the service boy bought me the juice. As i am suffering from diabetic problem. I have some limitation in consuming sugar per day. Cause of this i ask him again is this juice is without sugar. Confidentially he said yes it is. On the first sip itself i felt a over sweetness. I called him and ask why is it taste over sweetness. His answer was so funny, they bought the best oranges from market and this time we got the sweetest one. I am not convinced by his reply. When the service person leaves from me i directly went to the juice maker and ask whether is it a without or with sugar juice. He told, i put sugar in it. I inform this to the person who in the cashier and paid the money and left with all my anger on that service person.
I had a very bad experience there. The staff's are also not good . The food here is also not good. And the people are also not nice. You won't get what u want to eat.
Good restaurant Near Railway station
A good place to have quality food.  Lot of variety snacks available. Good service too
Best food and good job I am loving it.. falooda is awesome flavour bakery item is also too good good test ab tak ka Kerala ka sabse accha restaurant Royal Food
Sharjah shake was super awesome nd that too @Rs 55/- Rest of items were ordinary..nothing special !

Much of the dishes reminds me of Ifthar but they do offer more varities of chips etc. Food is okay enough but I don't find anything very special about it to comment on it. I believe they are known for their snacks.
Good service,but all items are not good .it's better in Navya bakers.
菜单品种不算多，这家特色是炸猪排！

Might be hard for first timers to spot the place because of low elevation of the hotel. Ample parking space for around 10 plus vehicles. They'll take around 30 minutes to serve you and be prepared accordingly. Favourite place for team lunches of Infopark employees. Mind you their serving size is big and you can do with one dish for two guys.
Serves South Indian as well as North Indian dishes.

A nice segregated dining place at the heart of kakkanad . Good people, good food and good ambience. I always had issues with its air conditioning. Transparent kitchen from outside a good garden at entrance. There is no USP of this place so nothing that can be considered or spoken about specifically. I have typically been having north Indian dishes here. Parking can be challenging sometimes as the connecting road is very narrow.

Good north indian food. A lot of variety to choose from. We visited this place as part of team lunch. There were 22 people in our team. As it was a busy day, there was a huge crowd and food took its own delay. But found most of the cuisine tasty. 
Parking is available for 6-7 cars and there is enough space on the road as well. The outdoor is well maintained

Ambience is really good. Staffs are good. There are lot of varieties of food available. But when it comes to taste of the food, It's just OK.
Not bad for sure. But there is nothing special about it.

Nice food especially rice items, Biriyani was good with large quantities offered in vessels. nice ambience and reasonable rates, staff courtesy is good. Takes time to process the order, cleanliness is top notch. Has good seating area outside for team lunch.

It's an old restaurant. Food is great.. They have maintained the taste over the yrs.... Menu has improved.... They have a pretty Cool lounge bar also. Excellent place to visit either with family or friends... Evening reserve seats by 7 :00 pm or lunch by 12 :45 pm as sometime u will have to wait if u come after the same.

I went for lunch with my parent. Everything from Ambience, service and food was great. The food was not very costly and you can feel the authentic taste in every item you order. The service was really fast and all the staff were really polite. Will definitely go there again when I visit Cochin again

A historic  hotel in Ernakulam MG Road,  near Jose junction. 
     Used to visit this place for having lunch or dinner when I visit Cochin . Their menu has a wide spread of veg as well as as non veg options .  The lunch here is very famous and normally there is a waiting time and hence prior booking of table is advisable . Their Pearl spot fish fry and other non veg varieties are finger licking. 
   Need to admit that the  food they serve is fresh and really tasty. This place attracts a sophisticated crowd. They have a bar and good parking space as well. 
    But, Yes ..  their menu is a bit expensive but  they serve good portions . However the Service is not so great especially during peak hours.

Grand Hotel is an excellent option for dining. This is one place we keep coming back to whenever we come to Cochin. The customer service is exemplary and the food is delicious. The staff members always make it a point to make one's visit a memorable one. They have ample parking space with free valet service. From the doorman to the waiters, everyone knows how to keep up the class of the hotel. Outstanding!

We had lunch from here today. Definitely one of the best restaurant in Cochin. Price is on the higher side. But that is reasonable considering the quality and service they offer. Average cost per person is 400 and above. Fish curry meals and appam is a must try.
Superb dishes. Garlic cheese naan is a must try. Loved the experience. Neat place , spacious. Service might need some improvement. But the food is worth the wait.

For a Dhaba, it's great. Food is fantastic and tasty. Service is great and friendly. Reasonably quick too. On the spicy side - newbies please note. But that's how most dhabas are... 
Charges are marginally on the higher side. But not a deal breaker.
Definitely worth a visit.

1 point less for an inaccessible restroom. (There's another, reasonably clean, wash basin within the restaurant area itself.) But surely they can do something about this omission.

Tasty food. I liked it. But NOT ideal for family dining. Apt for dining with male colleges. A dhaaba ambience. We felt so insecure due to the rough body language of staff members, and young friends of the manager were roaming around.
I love the food here. Good service also. One dhaba style food.
Cool place to hang.. food can be better
Awesome dhaba.. nice punjabi touch to everything here.. the music.. the people.. feels like mini punjab..
Unfortunately, the dhabha has closed now...!!! :(

Yeah.its good it's not so big and normal place for good food. Neat and clean. Variety of vegetarian food is available here, idli, dosas,  chappathies and other small snacks in varieties available as a treat for munching on the way. A Good place. Food also tasty, clean and good.👌😍😆

Nice and tasty food. I ordered special veg thali and it tastes superb. Everything was tasty in the thali. Price was also reasonable. I recommend this restaurant to everyone. Thank you sharma restaurant for the wonderful thali
A better place for exploring north Indian food in  the middle of the citys busy market.
The second best in Kochi after Punjab house. Must try restaurant even if you are non-vegetarian. Open till 11pm and more variety available compared to Punjab house
Great place for north indian dishes and foods at reasonable rate
Good place to have Chinese food. They have more options.
Very nice and comprehensive service. I recommend
The food is good! I used to go on Sundays once upon a time for buffet! The variety and the quality is very good. It is inexpensive too
nice clean spacios place to have a good meal
Very open and bright. Lots of light inside and big windows.
Frequented this place a lot. Good  continental selection at local rates. Avoid fish items. Everything else is brilliant and consistent.
It was good meal I had.... I think it's 1 of the best resto in town. "worth the visit"
They don't know how should a juicy steak be made!!!! very poor food
It closed :-(

Excellent vegetarian restaurant. Good ambience. Ample car parking. Food were really tasty. Staffs are good and shows good hospitality to customers. Clean and green hotel premises. Place is kept neat and tidy. Restrooms are clean. Excellent choice to spend evening time with your family.

a paradise indeed, for the nature lover. Set in a sprawling, lush green, five acre property overlooking the tranquil backwaters of Cochin, the resort has its own fresh water lake within its premises. Conceptualized to blend in with nature, BTH Sarovaram is in perfect harmony with its surroundings, enabling guests to indulge in the glory of nature.BTH Sarovaram provides all amenities for travelers on business or leisure, your home away from home.

Traditional Kerala meal on banana leaf was tasty and healthy. The atmosphere at the restaurant was calm and serene. Quick and friendly service. Vegetarian meals only. Lodging also available. Centrally located in Kochi.

A quaint place for stay on the Ernakulam Bypass near Kundanoor. The building is baker model built and the rooms have a coziness to them and is welcoming. The hotel construction is spread out instead of being one tall structure. Except the capsule rooms the rest are spacious and well furnished. Their restaurant is also pretty good and the food is tasty, but only vegetarian. There is ample car parking facility inside this compound. A highly recommended place.

Good location, very close to highway. It's a veg restaurant and the starters are good. It was not a good experience when coming to the main courSe curry dishes. Ambience is really good and worth spending a time with family in the evenings.

Better they close the non vegetarian purple restaurant
Nothing untoward happened only thing the food was not up to mark. Even the fish menu was not a Kerala delicacy. Having lived in Kerala and tried many places I would think twice to visit here.  My suggestion is to improve the taste. The vegetarian restaurant is standard and maintains it's taste for years.
Old charm lost. Lazy service and very slow. Food not as good as before. Sad
Located on M G Road, Cochin, North of Pallimukku junction. Good vegetarian food. Their buffet lunch is also good.
It's an reasonable priced hotel and located very near to Ernakulam jn station. Staff is good. Rooms are good.
One of the best restaurants for having a Dosa. Very attentive staffs. Able to identify their old customers.

One of the best premium vegetarian restaurants in the city. Vegetarian North Indian - Chinese - Jain foods are available. Nice ambience, service and facilities. Usually busy in the evenings specially on holidays.

Overhyped. The South Indian dishes, and lunch are poorly prepared. The waiters don't like it, and act all sophisticated if you order the simple stuff and don't go all complicated over the menu. There are plenty of other places that will give good quality food at the similar prices, and with better service.

Food was nice. Parking not available.  In fact they didn't let two wheeler inside the compound.  Had to park my bike roadside. Let me clarify.... The security person asked me to park the bike outside.
I had the north Indian thali and it was so so delicious. The staff were really friendly and I had a really tasty, wonderful experience. Would highly recommend!

I am reducing my rating from 5star to 2star.. due to bad quality.. from last 4visit I am confident that something had happened to his hotel.  All plus point s are gone.. now it's an average hotel.. with expensive price..

Was very impressed! Good food, great for sharing. Highly suggest getting three or four items and sharing. Our friends like the yogurt drinks. 
Bonus, they have a great yard that our kids could all run around in and we can watch them form the tables.
A good place for Asian foods.

The best Indian food that I've had in all of east Africa.  Service was friendly and fast! The waiters were very quick to refill drinks.  Dinner in most other restaurants took about 2.5hrs. As a party of four here, we were served within 20 minutes and were done within 1hr 30.  We ended up eating here twice because it was so good.
Best restaurant in the world. I’m drooling now just thinking about it. Fast service, good food, friendly staff.
The food smell so good!! 👌
Awesome place. Service is real good. Food tastes good. Friendly staff. Drinks available. They have daily offers on drinks. Make sure to check out the outside boards for offers.
Wine on the menu not available! Really shocking. Incomprehensible for a luxury hotel. Service below par.
Their afternoon brunch on Sundays is a feast fit for royals - everything is always perfect!
Wonderful ambiance , really sublime fine dining experience
nice place
Good place with a nice covered and air-conditioned outdoor style seating. The food was OK at best. No alcohol or beer.
Really good food. Great ambiance where the staff is courteous and nice. You get all sorts of food. The portions are small but delicious. And be prepared to spend 1000 or above for two people.
Such a nice place with good interior and cozy atmosphere.. the food the serve are really tasty and have good quality too... Its a place that we would love to visit again and again amd again...
Really tasty for what it is. I came here one night when I couldn’t sleep at 5 am. And I was blown away by this 24 hour restaurant !
It has a good ambience and all, but the staff there are not at all helpful. The food is awesome though.
Food feels likw homely and pure.
Super food
Good place for breakfast.

This place as usual is exceptional and I find myself going to it at least once a week. It is very reasonably priced, the service is always very prompt and the lamb korma curry is the best I've had.

If you like spicy food you can't go wrong with this place, (I recommend asking for 4 stars if you like a good heat) but the food stands out on it's own even with no stars.

Will definitely continue to make this one of my frequent stops on the island.
Some of the best Indian food I've had. We ordered especially mild, due to a young child with us, and the food was served exactly as requested. I will positively eat here again.

The service was great. I was not impressed by the food. It was not Indian food. I think the owner outsourced the preparation to someone besides Indian. There was Tofu on the menu. And I've never seen that before in a authentic Indian restaurant.But the service was great!
We've only ordered take out and find their food enjoyable considering the limited choices on the island for exotic flavors.
Good selection of Indian food at affordable prices. Relaxed casual atmosphere

My favourite place to hang out around here. The food here really is the best. The Kashi Art Cafe might get all the hype, but the food here is way better. The potatoe wedges are a must try! The omelettes too are amazing. And the honey dipped French toast was simply out of the world. Loved the cold coffee and the ginger ice tea. Absolute value for money!
Good ambience. Their chocolate cake is their star attractive. Their pasta is a must try. However the staff take forever to complete the orders.
I keep coming back for their cafe latte! A relaxing place to eat and good value for money. Their white sauce shrimp pasta and french toast are amazing!

Great place. Had breakfast there during our stay at Fort Kochi. Also visited for a late lunch once. 

Very good food, everything is freshly prepared so a bit slow. 

Friendly staff and great service overall.

Nice ambience with indoor and outdoor seating areas

We tried the chocolate cake, the pineapple juice,  the cold coffee and the lemon cake. All of them were really good but then I tried the french toast... That was AMAZING, the best french toast I've ever had.

The food served here is pretty good. But i am not a fan of their cold coffees which seems to be watery. Also you end up having to make your own drink. But you should definitely try any of the food on the menu and I'm sure you would leave here a happy person.

Very expensive. I only ordered the chocolate cake and a few drinks. Everything was delicious, no doubt about that. The juices were very fresh. The cake is kind of very big for one person😅 not complaining 🤭. Overall a good place with a very cozy Vibe to spend the evening with a bunch of friends.❣️
Very beautiful ambiance. Went early in morning yet staff was well dressed and attentive.  Very less waiting time between orders.  Amazing taste. Bit extensive Yet Totally worth it.

Great ambience..  Great taste..  Great hospitality..  Must visit place..  Might have to wait a bit as there is too much people wanting for a seat..  But its worth the wait...  Speedy service.  Always full of foreigners..

What a place this is! An old courtyard house adaptively reused as a cafe, a perfect example of how a domestic place of historic value can be used creatively. The food is always good. Ate there twice and never disappointed. They can sometime take a little longer than u expect, but it is worth the wait totally! Best part is they open at 8:30 am

Very bad restaurant with a very high waiting time. I have only went 2 times and had to wait for more than 30 mins. The attitude of the waiters are also very bad. They once charged for a dish that was not ordered.

The price for the dishes are also high.

Over all a totally useless place.
Even Arabs wouldn't have a double taste as its authenticity is high with mere quality Persian spices.

Its good for team dinner. Foods are normal qualily and moderate rates.

For getting food minimum 30 mint will take....

Quaint café in a family residence filled with antique kettles, great colour plan, antique furniture and a warm ambience. Go for the ambience and the pot tea prepared and served in the old fashioned way. The teas are single plantation and the flavour is amazing. Give the milk and sugar a miss for once and enjoy the real taste of tea. You'll love it😍

Fantastic place! Good coffee, good food (had a sandwich and samosas), good and friendly service, spotlessly clean and all with a beautiful ambience in an old colonial style building. Sure it's a bit more expensive than a chai on the street but the prices are reasonable and absolutely justified.
I like the ambience here. An Earl Grey tea and slice of cheesecake 👌. Breakfast is good too and the toasted tuna sandwich

The ambience invites you to spent extended hours here, all spent in the company of good food. 

The entire package is made all the more sweeter by the pricing. 

I’m surprised the place has been operational since fourteen years and I’m stumbling upon in now.

My favourite place in the whole of Kochi. The Tea and teatime snacks are delicious (orange cake, banana pancakes get special mention) - the place is quiet, airy and beautiful with antique tea memorabilia everywhere you look.
